All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
Bullets
Should contain a list of all bullets in the game.
Canvas
Represents a canvas, which contains graphical functions, inputs processing, and world updating.
Effects
Should contain a list of all visual effects that can be created in the game.
Enemies
Should contain a list of all enemies in the game.
Entity
Represents an entity, which can be instantiated with a type declared in Bullets of Enemies to control its behavior.
Main
Contains the main method, which sets up the project.
Sprites
Should contain a list of all Sprites in the game.
Table
Represents a basic table, which will be the superclass of all UI.
Type
Represents a type of entity, and will be the superclass of all BulletTypes and EnemyTypes.
Vars
Contains many static fields, all of which are contents either essential to the program itself of determining important aspects of the program.
